00:00:21.100 --> 00:00:25.180
First up - Valve has announced Steam Family
Sharing - this long-awaited and often-rumored

00:00:25.180 --> 00:00:29.320
feature lets friends and family members borrow
each others' games - basically your friend

00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:31.630
can authorize your computer to play his game.

00:00:31.630 --> 00:00:36.170
Then you get to earn your own Steam achievements
and save your own progress to the Steam cloud.

00:00:36.170 --> 00:00:39.860
So then theoretically if you borrow a friend's
game and later decide to buy it yourself,

00:00:39.860 --> 00:00:42.089
you should be able to pick back up on your
progress.

00:00:42.089 --> 00:00:46.210
The feature will go into beta sometime this
month - to sign up, join the Family Sharing

00:00:46.210 --> 00:00:50.610
Group on the steam community, and Valve will
choose an initial pool of 1000 Steam accounts

00:00:50.610 --> 00:00:52.440
from this group to try it out.

00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:57.000
FINALLY, one of the biggest advantages console
gaming had over Steam, but Valve's catching

00:00:57.000 --> 00:00:58.000
up now!

00:00:58.000 --> 00:00:59.000
What do you guys think?

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:00.049
